The circumference of a circle with radius $\blueD{r}= \blueD{6371}\text{ km}$ is

$\begin{align}
 \maroonD{C} 
&=2\pi \blueD{r}  \\[2mm]
&=2\pi (\blueD{6371}\text{ km}) \\[2mm]
&= 12742\pi \text{ km}
\end{align}$

The circumference of a circle with diameter of $\blueD{20}\text{ m}$ is:

$\begin{align}
\maroonD{C} 
&=\pi \blueD{d}  \\[2mm]
&=\pi (\blueD{20}\text{ m}) \\[2mm]
&= \blueD{20\pi} \text{ m}
\end{align}$

To find the diameter of the lake we must solve for $\greenD{d}$ in the following equation 

$\begin{align*}
  \pi \greenD{d} &= \blueD{C} \\[1mm]
\pi \greenD{d} 	&= \blueD{400\pi}\text{ m} \\[1mm]
  \cancel{\pi} \greenD{d} 	
&= 400\cancel{\pi}\text{ m} \\[1mm] 
  \greenD{d} &= 400\text{ m}
\end{align*}$

The circumference of a circle with radius $\maroonD{r}=\maroonD{30.1} \text{ AU}$ is:

$\begin{align}
\blueD{C}&=2\pi\maroonD{r} \\
&=2\pi(\maroonD{30.1}) \\
&=\blueD{60.2\pi}
\end{align}$

