The diameter of the pipe is $\greenD{20}\text{ cm}$. Since the radius of a circle is half the length of the diameter, we can divide to find the radius:

$\begin{align}
\maroonD{r}  &= \dfrac{\greenD{20}}{2}  \\\\
\maroonD{r}   &= \maroonD{10}\text{ cm}
\end{align}$

The diameter $\goldE{d}$ of a circle is twice as long as its radius $\greenD{r}$.

$\begin{align}
\goldE{d}&=2\greenD{r} \\
\goldE{d}&=2(\greenD{22}) \\
\goldE{d}&=\goldE{44}
\end{align}$

